The paper proposes a new algorithm for adversarial training, which is a common technique used in machine learning for improving the robustness of neural networks. The paper focuses on improving the generalization of adversarial training, which is a key challenge in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with security and privacy issues related to adversarial attacks, it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
